Done! I've created a comprehensive integration test suite for OpenPrint Cloud. Here's what was added:

## Files Created

**`tests/integration/api_test.go`** - Main test file with:
- Health check tests for all 5 services (table-driven)
- Database connection and table validation
- Auth service tests (register, login, get user, unauthorized, duplicate email)
- Registry service tests (agents, printers, heartbeat, status updates)
- Job service tests (create, list, queue stats)
- Storage service tests (upload, list, metadata)
- End-to-end workflow test covering the complete print job lifecycle
- Docker container communication tests
- Concurrent request handling tests
- WebSocket endpoint availability test

**`tests/integration/README.md`** - Documentation with:
- Prerequisites and setup instructions
- How to run tests
- Environment variable configuration
- Test coverage overview
- Troubleshooting guide

## Test Results Summary

**Passing (6/11 test suites):**
- ✅ TestHealthChecks - All 5 services
- ✅ TestDatabaseConnection - PostgreSQL + 7 tables
- ✅ TestAuthServiceEndpoints - Register, login, get user
- ✅ TestConcurrentRequests - Concurrent health checks
- ✅ TestWebSocketConnection - WebSocket endpoint
- ✅ TestServiceAvailability - Service availability check

**Failing (5/11)** - These reveal service implementation issues:
- Registry agent registration returns 500 (likely needs `organization_id`)
- Cascading failures in job, storage, and E2E tests

## Running the Tests

```bash
# Ensure services are running
cd deployments/docker && docker-compose up -d

# Run integration tests
go test ./tests/integration/ -v

# Run specific test
go test ./tests/integration/ -v -run TestHealthChecks
```
